# 8. 壁は、はるか高く

Nagi: <Thanks, everyone!>
Kohane: ...
Kohane: (This is it...)
Kohane: (This is what happened during RAD WEEKEND.)
Kohane: (How do I even begin to describe it...?)
Kohane: (It's sent my heart into overdrive... No, more than that...)
Kohane: (It shook the entire world. It was really that kind of event.)
Kohane: (This might be the true definition of “exhilaration”...)
An: Man, that's so unfair...
An: It just completely blew apart the way I remembered everything. My heart's still racing...
Akito: Same... A part of me was wondering if I was seeing this event through rose-colored glasses...
Akito: But it really was just that incredible.
Toya: I have a much better understanding of what you've all been telling me now...
Toya: Even as a video, it can hit us this hard...
Len: <Th-That was so cool...!>
Len: <RAD WEEKEND really was as amazing as everyone was saying...!>
Miku: <Yeah...>
Miku: (So this is RAD WEEKEND...)
Miku: (This is the wall they face...)
An's Father: So, what did you think of RAD WEEKEND?
An's Father: Think you can surpass it...?
Kohane: ...!
Kohane: Surpass this...?
Kohane: I can't say for sure...
Kohane: It exceeded all of my expectations... I sort of can't believe something like this actually happened...
Kohane: It's... Scary...
Taiga: ...
Kohane: But...
Kohane: I feel more excited about this than before.
Kohane: I feel even more determined to surpass RAD WEEKEND now. So...
Kohane: We will... We absolutely will!
An's Father: Alright...
An: Way to go, Kohane!! That's my partner for you!!
An: And you finally got a taste of what I felt that night!
Kohane: Yeah!
Toya: We'll probably have to clear quite a few hurdles and jump through countless hoops to get there...
Toya: But I believe we can do it.
Akito: Yeah.
Akito: We're gonna show everyone who's boss!
Kohane: Aoyagi, Shinonome...
Kohane: Yeah...!
Kohane: (We can do it... We're gonna surpass RAD WEEKEND!!)
Len: We're back!!
Miku: MEIKO, we're back...
MEIKO: Welcome back, you two. You were gone quite a while.
MEIKO: Lay it on me. What was the venue for RAD WEEKEND like?
Miku: It was nice... The owner seemed to take very good care of it.
Len: But something more amazing happened! Not only did we see the venue, we actually got to see RAD WEEKEND!!
MEIKO: Huh? What do you mean?
Miku: We discovered that there was a recording of it, and we even got to watch it.
MEIKO: ...! You're kidding!
MEIKO: What was it like?
Len: It was... I dunno... Really, really amazing!
Len: Everyone there gave it absolutely everything they had. Almost as if it was the last show they were all doing, you know...?
Len: No, wait... That's not doing it justice...
MEIKO: Hehe. I think I understand a little. It was so incredible that it's too difficult to put into words, no?
Miku: ...
MEIKO: Miku...?
Miku: Yes, it was an incredible event...
Miku: But...
Miku: It wasn't just that.
MEIKO: It was more...?
Miku: Something along those lines...
Miku: (I have to think RAD WEEKEND has a special place in the hearts of countless people.)
Miku: (Surpassing that means somehow also surpassing what everyone felt that night...)
Miku: (I can't even begin to imagine what that entails...)
Kohane: (Think about what you saw... Focus on what you've absorbed...)
Kohane: (How big was the live house...? How many people were in the audience...?)
Kohane: (And...)
Nagi: ♪————————!!
Kohane: (Just like her...!)
Kohane: ♪————————!!
Kohane: Huff... Huff...! H-How was that?
Toya: We came here expecting to see how you've progressed since you started working with Taiga, but to see this kind of change...
Toya: It's as if you somehow placed yourself in that video.
Kohane: R-Really?
Kohane: Do you think actually seeing how everything looked from the stage has anything to do with it?
Toya: From the stage? What do you mean?
Kohane: So, when I was practicing with Taiga...
An: Wait, that's what you guys have been doing...?
An: Hehe... But we're not letting you get away so easily.
Akito: Yeah, I agree.
Akito: Alright, let's get to it!
An: Yeah!! Kohane!!
Kohane: Eep! Y-Yes, An?
An: Mind telling us more about what you've been doing with Uncle Taiga? That's okay, right?
Kohane: Yeah, sure!
Kohane: While working with him, I learned that...
